fr.groupe40.projet.model.planets

Class Planet

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.groupe40.projet.model.Sprite
      • fr.groupe40.projet.model.planets.Planet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RoundPlanet, SquarePlanet

    public abstract class Planet
extends Sprite
    This class is meant to define a new Object Planet, which is not instanciable due to the toString abstract method. Planet is an Abstract class of the general type "planet". Planets are defined by a user, and they all have a different produce rate. Each planets can be selected, and own a number of troops with a specific ship type.
    Author:
    Jordane Masson, Sarah Portejoie
    See Also:
    RoundPlanet, SquarePlanet, Serialized Form
